answers.answer: Idk but I've had them too!!
It's a headache. Sorry to tell you lol. You've got a lot of blood and pressure pumping through you. Headaches are normal.

If you are getting them often check your blood pressure, it can be a sign of preeclampsia. I would let your doctor know. I just had my baby Thursday, 2 days short of 37 weeks because of this. It was so bad try had to take her early :( hopefully it's just a plain old headache for you but I would definitely make sure!

Since I turned 37 weeks I've been having migraines. I'm very sensitive to light and sound. I can't take anything but it's so uncomfortable. Worse part 2 days ago I had a really bad nosebleed after my headache started.  I went in to the hospital,  they monitored baby and said he is fine. I just developed migraines )= not sure they will go away after delivery.  I thought maybe it was related to blood pressure but my blood pressure is fine. Dr said a couple more weeks and hopefully it will be and thing of the past.  Hoping so.
